results.name: Number of factorizations of n into factors > 1 with different sums of prime indices. Number of multiset partitions of the multiset of prime indices of n with distinct block-sums.
comment: A prime index of n is a number m such that prime(m) divides n. The multiset of prime indices of n is row n of A112798. The sum of prime indices of n is A056239(n).
link: Gus Wiseman, Sequences counting and ranking multiset partitions whose part lengths, sums, or averages are constant or strict.
